WEBVTT

00:00:12.820 --> 00:00:19.219
While waiting to appear before Caesar, the Apostle Paul spent two years in Rome under house arrest.

00:00:20.379 --> 00:00:27.780
There he was guarded by Roman soldiers who probably belonged to an elite military force called the Pretorian Guard.

00:00:28.420 --> 00:00:34.280
The most important role was protecting the Emperor himself.

00:00:34.880 --> 00:00:45.060
The Pretorian Guard was organized for this purpose in 27 BCE by Caesar Augustus.

00:00:47.399 --> 00:00:54.439
In 23 CE, Emperor Tiberius ordered the Guard to establish a permanent camp on the outskirts of Rome.

00:00:56.039 --> 00:00:58.439
This complex was called the Castropritoria.

00:01:01.479 --> 00:01:10.480
Even though there were thousands of Pretorian soldiers, all told the Philippine congregation that his prison bonds had become known by all the Pretorian Guard.
